    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-06T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-06T21:00:00-05:00" n="57"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d57">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/552: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hornibrook</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-06T20:00:00-06:00"
                            >September 6, 1937—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 7—12:04 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>59. Following week-end surge of public sentiment favorable to such action and
                    apparently after consultation with Salvador, Costa Rican Government late this
                    afternoon offered mediation to Nicaragua and Honduras.</p>
                <p>Reports from Managua indicate that conflict was in process of adjustment before
                    this step taken.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hornibrook</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
